6:
Come on, Tanky! You can't just
break up the streets all willy-nilly like
that! Do you WANT to make me
angry?
9:
Well, this DOES happen every time,
but still! That doesn't mean we
shouldn't be careful!
12:
Come in, Chief! Can you hear me?
Are you okay?
16:
Hey, old man! Better call the
insurance company! The two of us
are making a REAL mess out here!
19:
Already done, Chief! But what about
you? Are you hurt?!
21:
Atta boy! You, sir, are the definition
of SPEED. And I'm totally fine!
24:
Nyahaha! What's the matter?
Throwing a tantrum 'cuz I'm not
paying attention to you? Heh... Not
like you have voice recognition
software anyway.
28:
Oho! Looks like my release code
came in! I can use my Chip D'éclat
in self defense now.
31:
Nyaha! You want some of this, big
boy? Then bring it on!
37:
Can't believe that little Love brat is
making us go somewhere in place
of her buddy...
41:
Come on, it's not that big of a deal.
We're getting paid, aren't we?
46:
The hell?! No one told me bionics
were gonna be involved! And my
release code's been blocked!
49:
Uh-oh, having trouble, missy? Well...
Looks like this is the end of the line
for you!
57:
That's not important! You need help,
right? We've got your back!
62:
Wait, are you guys troubleshooters?!
Perfect timing! I've got a job for you,
right here, RIGHT NOW!
73:
Nyahaha! How the tables have
turned! Ain't no rules about beating
up a machine!
78:
Another job well-done! Thanks for
your help! Who knew such capable
troubleshooters were just waiting
around the corner!
82:
Nah, you're the one who's something
else... But wait, aren't you a
troubleshooter yourself?
86:
Ah, weeell, not quite. I work for 3MM
Security as—
89:
Chief! I finally caught up to you! Are
you hurt anywhere?!
92:
Nyahaha, see for yourself!
Ah, by the way, the only thing here 
I took down is the tank! 
I didn't touch the bionics!
95:
Uh... Okay, I think I see what
happened here. Did you employ the
help of these troubleshooters?
99:
Well, yeah! What else was I
supposed to do when all these
bionics showed up outta nowhere?!
My code was blocked!
103: Um... Did we do something wrong?
106:
No, not at all! We're very grateful for
your help. We will, of course,
compensate you for your time.
109:
You bet! Ah, but there is some
paperwork you gotta fill out, so...
mind dropping by the office with us?
115:
All right, you guys are all clear!
Thanks and nice to meet you, Alk
and Nimbus!
119:
Um... Ms. Tink, right? They called you
the chief back there. Does that
make you—
121:
Yup, I'm the head honcho around
here. See? It even says so on my
employee badge.
124: And you can just call me Tink, silly.
129:
Err, it's just that... you don't exactly
give off that... corporate vibe, if you
know what I mean. What's the name
of this place again?
132:
We're the Special Equipment
Defense Force. That might sound
fancy, but we're mostly a bunch of
old codgers headed to retirement.
We're the lowest of the low at 3MM.
134:
Yeah, and thanks to our overzealous
boss, our reviews are always the
worst of the worst too.
142:
So you mainly deal with combat,
right? You don't seem to have a lot
of people though...
145:
Well, we're a bit different from other
combat-centric teams. The chief
here is the only one who fights. The
rest of us are what you could call...
damage control.
149:
Yeah, they deal with the stuff I break.
Can't fight properly when I'm too
busy holding back.
153:
Nyahaha! And thanks to me, our
department's performance scores
are the top of the company! As long
as I get my release code, I'm
UNSTOPPABLE!
157:
You mentioned that code during the
battle too. What is it, exactly?
161:
Well, you see... In order for me to use
the battle assistance chip installed
in me, I need to get permission from
the company.
163:
It's called my Chip D'éclat. It
basically removes any limits on my
power output and allows me to go
into overdrive!
166:
Research on the chip was
abandoned due to the danger it
presented. The only one permitted
to use it out of anyone in the Noxel
Group is our chief.
169:
Yeah, 'cuz no one else has the right
genetic makeup for it. Everyone else
either breaks down or ends up
paralyzed... So yeah, it's SUPER
dangerous.
173:
So... The reason you were cornered
was because you couldn't use it,
right?
177:
Exactly. If I attack without
permission, I'd be labeled a
criminal....
181:
Which is why it's so weird that I
couldn't attack! I had authorization
and everything!
184:
It is very strange indeed... And the
number of such instances has
increased recently...
186:
Chief... Perhaps we should also join
you in battle.
189:
Nyahaha! Not THAT again! I told you,
I'm fine by myself! Leave the heavy
stuff to your boss!
192:
But... I get the feeling someone is
blocking your code intentionally.
And no third party should be able to
hack our systems like that.
194:
I will admit something fishy's going
on. If Alk and Nimbus hadn't shown
up, I would've had to retreat—
198:
Wait, now that I'm looking at you
two, I don't see any prosthetics on
you... Are you two all natural? There's
no way...
201:
Well, I guess we are. We don't have
any prosthetics.
206:
Whoa, seriously?! You're ORGANICS?!
How are you so strong, then?!
210:
Well, let's just say we're... out of this
world? But you're the amazing one,
Tink! I can't believe you're a chief at
your age!
214:
Hehe, pretty cool, right? Still, you two
have great potential...
218:
Which is why I'm using my power as
chief to officially recruit you to our
department!
223:
Couldn't help yourself, huh... What
do you think, Alk? I don't care either
way.
227:
Weeell, it's probably more profitable
than the Kaleidoscope...
231:
Nyahaha! Sounds like we've got
ourselves some new teammates!
234: I can't wait to put you two to work!
